<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">21. Marx, Ellen. Optical Color and Simultaneity. Translated by Geoffrey Oâ€™Brien. New York: Van Nostrand Reinhold, 1983. 152 pp. Endnotes/footnotes, B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-442-23864-9.</p><p class="annot">Psychological and physiological aspects of optical color are approached through an exceptional collection of designed visuals that demonstrate optical and subtractive complements, successive contrast, and the opposing color effects of simultaneous contrast and optical mixture. The reader views 100 color pages produced through superb five-color printing (CYMK plus green), on which 24 color-printed acetate overlays can be superimposed. The straightforward text complements the illustrations and explains complex ideas clearly for its intended audience of art and design professionals and students.</p></div>
